    "side_effects_description": "The possible side effects of using Meehania fargesii improperly are that it can cause nausea due to its emmenagogue properties, exacerbate allergies as it belongs to the Lamiaceae family, which includes plants known to trigger allergic reactions, induce nausea and trigger asthma in susceptible individuals, particularly those with pre-existing respiratory conditions, and experience nausea is also a reported side effect likely due to its potential interaction with certain medications or sensitivities.",
    "uses": "Meehania fargesii is a plant native to China, and it has been used in traditional medicine for various purposes. The plant's leaves and stems are used to treat fever, rheumatism, and digestive issues. Traditionally, it is also used to lower blood pressure and as an anti-inflammatory agent. However, more research is needed to confirm its effectiveness and safety for human consumption. In some regions, it is also used as a natural remedy for snake bites and insect stings.",
    "taxonomy": "Meehania fargesii is classified in the following way: it belongs to the family Lamiaceae, commonly known as the mint family. The genus Meehania is a small group of flowering plants native to East Asia. Meehania fargesii is specifically a species of flowering plant native to China. It is a perennial herb, often found growing in shady woodland environments. Meehania fargesii is also known by the common name Farges' meehania.",
    "benefits": "Meehania fargesii.  Meehania fargesii is a plant traditionally used in Chinese medicine, and it may have various health benefits, including anti-inflammatory, antioxidant, and antimicrobial properties. It may also be used to treat fever, cough, and respiratory issues. Studies have shown that the plant's extracts may have neuroprotective effects and may help in reducing the risk of age-related neurodegenerative diseases. However, more research is needed to confirm the full extent of its health benefits.",
    "parts": "Meehania fargesii. The medicinal parts of Meehania fargesii, commonly known as Farges' meehania, are the leaves, stems, and roots. Traditionally, these parts are used in herbal medicine to treat various ailments, including fever, inflammation, and respiratory issues. The leaves are particularly valued for their anti-inflammatory properties, while the roots are used to treat digestive problems. Further research is needed to confirm the full extent of Meehania fargesii's medicinal properties and potential uses.",
    "intro": "Meehania fargesii, also known as Farges' meehania or Chinese meehania, is a perennial herbaceous plant native to China, belonging to the Lamiaceae family. It has been traditionally used in medicine to treat various health issues, including fever, cough, and respiratory problems, due to its anti-inflammatory and antimicrobial properties, which may contribute to its potential health benefits such as reducing inflammation and improving respiratory function. The bioactive constituents of Meehania fargesii include flavonoids, phenolic acids, and terpenoids, which are thought to be responsible for its medicinal properties. In traditional Chinese medicine, Meehania fargesii is commonly prepared into teas, infusions, and extracts, which are used to treat various health conditions, and is also sometimes used in combination with other herbs to enhance its therapeutic effects."
